rity\\nNo security vulnerabilities or leaked secrets were found. Identity preservation follows the existing file-based persistence model.\\n\\n## Quality\\nThe code is well-structured and follows the project's architectural standards. The integration tests provide high confidence in the behavioral correctness of the gating mechanism.\\n\\n## Issues Found\\n- None.\\n\\n## Verdict: PASS\\n\\n## Notes for Lead Agent\\nThe implementation is solid and meets all acceptance criteria. The addition of `tests/test_role_gate_integration.py` is a valuable regression anchor for the render pipeline.\\n\"}}\n./sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260416T054258Z_1776356839.log:- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\n./sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260416T054258Z_1776356839.log:- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\n./sdp/templates/candidates/verify/v001.md:- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\n./sdp/templates/candidates/verify/v001.md:- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\n./sdp/templates/candidates/verify/v002.md:- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Startup hardening gap: `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py` does not call `bootstrap_identity()` before startup announcement and main loop, while this path is still part of the runnable daemon entry points (`my-claw/docs/PROJECT_GUIDE.md` and system scripts/tests reference it), so first-boot identity creatio